Can you imagine how simple and amazingly beautiful lives of a village, considering what we have here. We live a pretty complicated and busy life where all of us would love to run away from it and hide in a peaceful place like this.

That’s why we picked this beautiful serene village near Belihuloya for you to hide from your busy life schedule.

Pick up your backpack, run away from your cozy life. We will guide you through a simplest of way of life for two days to live in a campsite situated in a waterfront. It’s a sort of a place where you are allowed to jump in to water at any time and in addition to that, a campfire will light up all along the night.

During the day we will arrange short hiking trips through paddy fields and nearby jungle, for you to experience the village and surrounding area. You can enjoy fresh fruits, like banana, papaya, guava, a kurumba or even a king coconut from a village garden.

You will smell the BBQ just after the sun down, come and rest yourself, we are waiting to welcome you!
Coffee is a essential part of camping, we always used to keep the kettle filled with water and hanging over the fire

We all love to have a tasty Coconut Juice. This one, named as "Kundira" in country side is something special. Its rich in Water though its small and tasty as nothing can be described with words.

I cannot stop these two guys having more than two and they even didn't waited till we get them ready to drink. They were delighted with the taste and continue their efforts to finish whole bunch of Coconuts.

Feel the true beauty of village life and walk through the paddy areas smelling the fragrance of dried paddy. (There is not much green left in most paddy areas, since It's the off season for paddy cultivation)

Asela and Ashan are work buddies and they decided to come to "Campers Lodge" along with their other office mates. They were the guides of the crew to march towards our camping area. Asela was the guy who wanted to hike more through wild and Ashan was more focus on finding the shortest way to Campsite.

Camping is not about comforts you experience in your day to day life. It's about living with average facilities and with heap of peace of mind. Most believe a good sleep is all about a fancy bedroom and a comfortable bed. Ashan found it in our hammock without any of those so-called fanciness or even the best of comforts.

Lighting up the campfire was one of the most exiting part of campers. Even we are exited too in that. I always used to take a good picture of every campfire at the start. Second step is hanging water filled kettle over fire to start up with a mug of coffee for all our guest campers. Though it's not that cold here, all of them loved to sit around the fire and sip their coffee while talking about their adventures hike towards campsite.

We all live in a rat race, we have forgotten what we have and what we should cherish and love. You do need to get away to relax your mind and soul to reminisce what you have and had. These two were lost in their memories fading in to the silence of the night. Fire kept them warm and the calm surrounding helped them to fall deeper and deeper
Drive way to our main house through the village
Morning sunshine giving it's blessings to the newly cultivated paddy fields.

Kids were so eager to fire up the big campfire we set at a corner of the campsite. They were so exited to see dancing flames and had thousands of questions even we didn't had answers to them. These three guys had a amazing time with us.

The Milky Way is crystal clear during nighttime, when the moon is weak.

The Greek name for the Milky Way (Γαλαξίας Galaxias) is derived from the Greek word for milk (γάλα, gala). According to Greek mythology, Heracles' father, Zeus, was fond of his son, who was born of the mortal woman Alcmene. He decided to let the infant Heracles suckle on his divine wife Hera's milk when she was asleep, an act which would endow the baby with godlike qualities. When Hera woke and realized that she was breastfeeding an unknown infant, she pushed him away and the spurting milk became the Milky Way.

In the Camp site,21 rowed Swiss Cottage tents are there with a kitchen & a dining.In the camp ground one can laze around and enjoy the panoramic view of the valley.

The camp is surrounded by rare herbs,unique trees & it offers you 360°
view.From your own camp balcony or lazing under canopy in the campground,you can have mesmerizing view over viewing  snow clad mountains,river Bhaga,glaciers,
beautiful meadows.
Rowed Swiss cottages engulfed by juniper trees....

With three layered insulated mat floored room with attached bathroom,6 to 6.30 feet adjustable cot,6 ' mattress,400 GSM quilt & pillow,100% woolen blankets,you can have a good sleep surrounded by buddhist lucky signs on the tent inner walls.
Camp site overlooking back of Glacier Lady of Keylong peak with river river Bhaga flowing beneath....

With three layered insulated mat floored room with attached bathroom,6 to 6.30 feet adjustable cot,6 ' mattress,400 GSM quilt & pillow,100% woolen blankets,you can have a good sleep surrounded by buddhist lucky signs on the tent inner walls.

Winter view from camp site.The glacier in the background accumulates snow year after year to form a glacier.And also the adjoining villages where you can come in winters for skying & other adventure activities  after the Rohtang tunnel opens up 2020.

Camping experience is inadequate without the campfire.Enjoying the warmth of the fire you can get a bit tipsy & can ask for minimum lights so to enjoy a little gupshap,a little dance around the the fire and the mesmerizing stargazing too.
Evenings are enjoyed around the bonfire with singing sessions too...

From canopy at camp ground too you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village Gemur to have an experience of the village life.

Lazing under canopy at camp ground you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village to have an experience of the village life.

Evening view are mesmerizing with sun setting & lights getting on.And the bone fire is also getting ready ! By this time you can ask for village cottage wheat wine locally made by the villagers if you wish to get a bit tipsy around the bone fire.....

The lily in the front of camp site.And a Glacier in the background accumulated through hundreds of years.These glaciers used to be huge 15 years back.Now it's receding fast.So be a messenger by spreading awareness about the fragile Himalayan ecology.

Sun setting snow peaked mountain view from campsite.This is the same way you would be going in the morning while heading to Leh-Ladakh.And if you rise early you would have something very similar when the sun is rising.

Night view of camp site.Flood lights are on only till all the guest are in.And then on we try to give you minimal lights so to enjoy the serene ambience & of course so to enjoy the stargazing.........
In the night we can minimize or even black out to have a wonderful stargazing.....

From your camp balcony you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village Gemur to have an experience of the village life.

butter tea.And sea-buckthorn (a wonder fruit) tea-our specialty.
View of Camp site valley in winters.

Hieno Sahakosken alue avautuu eteesi! Satakunnan kauneimpia koskimaisemia!
Tentsilellä nukkuessasi, leijut puiden välissä ja nautit luonnosta öttiäisten pysyessä ulkopuolella, sekä ilmasta, että maasta!
Haluatko lähteä tutustumaan alueen luontoon, tai vaikkapa kalastamaan? Vene on vapaasti käytössäsi ilman lisämaksuja ja odottaa sinua rannassa!
Tentsile puumajoite on mahtava, irti maasta reilusti! On elämys viettää yö puumajoitteessa!
Mukava köllötellä perin hyvässä asennossa ja nautiskella luonnon rauhasta, suojassa hyttysiltä ja muilta ötököiltä!

Kuva otettu kovalla sadeilmalla, puusto suojaa hyvin aluetta ja sadesuoja viimeistelee vielä pöytäryhmän yläpuolella, iltaa voi istua aivan kuivana. Tentsilessä on kuvassa päällä sadesuoja, joka antaa täyden suojan sateelta!
Sahakoski virtaa vuolaana, sanotaan että ihminen rentoutuu ja voi hyvin metsissä ja virtaavien koskien läheisyydessä, luonnon energia todella tuntuu!
Tukeva ja vakaa vene käytössäsi, moottorivene-mallinen on soutuveneenäkin tukevampi vesillä, ei kallistele niin helposti kuin ns. Perinteinen soutuvene! Turvallista menoa!

Käytössäsi on mukavuuksia, sähköä laitteiden, kuten puhelimen ja tabletin lataukseen. Jääkaappi, mikro, vedenkeitin ja kahvinkeitin. Juomavettä sekä käsienpesuvettä. Vaahtosammutin kuuluu myös vastuulliseen retkeilyyn, kaiken varalta!
Pallogrilli ja hiiliä, sekä sytytysnestettä löytyy, ei tarvitse raahata mukanaan isoa pussia hiiliä, täältä löytyy välineet grillaamiseen.
Tentsile-puumajoite leijuu puiden välissä, nauti autenttisessa luonnossa rentoutuen kosken rauhallista soljuntaa kuunnellen.

Nauti ulkoporealtaassa höyryävän lämpimästä kylvystä, 2 hengen porealtaassa kauniin kosken rannalla. Porealtaan saat käyttöösi 20€ koko illaksi! Allas desinfioidaan ja vesi vaihdetaan jokaisen käyttökerran yhteydessä! Tee varaus etukäteen!

Souda veneellä iltasella ja näe majava iltauinnilla! Kuvassa oikealla on pitkäaikainen harvinaisen Euroopanmajavan pesä, Satakunnassa melko yleinen, muualla Suomessa harvinainen. Eruroopanmajava on Suomen alkuperäislajistoa!
